        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 8:20AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 820 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 8 miles southeast of Sagerton, moving southeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Haskell, Stamford, Anson, Avoca, Lake Stamford Marina, Paint Creek,
Funston, and Tuxedo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
